varargs status apply_status_effect(int effect, int strength, int duration,
 object source, status silent)

Apply one living-owned status effect from <status_effects.h>. effect must be
one exact STATUS_* bit. duration is in seconds; Burning ignores duration and
derives its lifetime from strength. source may be 0.
Set silent when refreshing or transforming an effect without application
messages. State and GMCP still update.

Named wrappers are preferred:
  apply_burning(int stacks, object source, status silent)
  apply_bleeding(int strength, int duration, object source, status silent)
  apply_chilled(int duration, object source, status silent)
  apply_freezing(int duration, object source, status silent)
  apply_exposed(int duration, object source, status silent)

Use query_status_effect(mask), query_status_effect_strength(effect),
query_status_effect_remaining(effect), query_status_effect_source(effect),
and remove_status_effect(mask, silent) to inspect or cure effects. See
`wizhelp 9.16` for stacking, caps, and lifecycle.
